			<STRING> (German IPA: [IPA: /ˈtsyːʁɪç/], in Zürich German Züri [IPA: [ˈtsyri]]; in English often Zurich) is the largest city in Switzerland (population: 366,145 in 2004; population of urban area: 1,091,732) and capital of the canton of Zürich.</STRING>
